---
import FleetMap from './FleetMap.tsx';

const tags = ['MapLibre', 'deck.gl', 'React'];
---

<section id="work">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Featured work</h2>

    <article class="card">
      <FleetMap client:idle />

      <div class="card-body">
        <h3>Fleet tracking at scale</h3>
        <p class="writeup">
          A live fleet-tracking map rebuilding the core of a production dispatch system: ~100
          vehicles moving along San Francisco's real street network — the underlying pipeline and
          rendering are built for thousands (see challenge 04); it's throttled here so individual
          GPS quirks stay legible — rendered with MapLibre GL and deck.gl's IconLayer.
        </p>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <span class="challenge-index">01</span>
          <strong>Stitching a noisy tracking feed</strong>
          <p>
            Real position feeds aren't clean: polls come back empty, re-send an already-seen tail,
            or — near tall buildings or in a tunnel — drift or drop out entirely. The merge step
            dedupes re-sent points, holds through empty polls, rejects lone bad pings, and accepts
            sustained relocations as real jumps:
          </p>

          <div class="diagram-tiles diagram-tiles-4">
            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 200 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: an overlapping tail of already-seen points gets deduped by timestamp">
                <path d="M80,45 Q105,32 130,45" class="dashed" />
                <line x1="15" y1="60" x2="185" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="30" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="60" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="90" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="120" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="150" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="170" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Overlap</strong>Re-sent tail deduped by timestamp.</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 200 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: an empty poll leaves the buffer holding at its last known point">
                <line x1="15" y1="60" x2="70" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="30" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="55" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="70" cy="60" r="8" class="pulse-ring" />
                <circle cx="70" cy="60" r="13" class="pulse-ring" />
                <line x1="70" y1="60" x2="120" y2="60" class="dashed" />
                <line x1="120" y1="60" x2="180" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="70" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="135" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="160" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="180" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Empty poll</strong>No new data — playback holds.</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 200 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: a sustained relocation after GPS loss is accepted as a jump and the trail breaks">
                <line x1="15" y1="65" x2="70" y2="65" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="30" cy="65" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="55" cy="65" r="4" class="dot" />
                <path d="M70,65 L115,25" class="dashed-accent" />
                <line x1="86" y1="52" x2="94" y2="40" class="break-tick" />
                <line x1="78" y1="44" x2="86" y2="32" class="break-tick" />
                <line x1="115" y1="25" x2="180" y2="25" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="115" cy="25" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="145" cy="25" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="180" cy="25" r="4" class="dot" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>GPS loss</strong>Sustained relocation — accepted jump, trail breaks.</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 200 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: a lone bad ping is rejected while the path stays straight">
                <line x1="15" y1="60" x2="185" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="30" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="65" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="100" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="135" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="170" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <line x1="100" y1="60" x2="100" y2="22" class="dashed" />
                <circle cx="100" cy="18" r="5" class="dot-rejected" />
                <line x1="96" y1="14" x2="104" y2="22" class="reject-mark" />
                <line x1="104" y1="14" x2="96" y2="22" class="reject-mark" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Bad ping</strong>Lone spike rejected — path stays straight.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <span class="challenge-index">02</span>
          <strong>Smoothing across update latency</strong>
          <p>Rendering the latest known position as it arrived caused a freeze-then-snap between updates; fixed with a playback delay so there's always a real buffered window to interpolate through.</p>

          <div class="diagram-tiles diagram-tiles-2">
            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 400 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: rendering the live edge freezes at the last known point, then snaps forward when new data arrives">
                <line x1="30" y1="60" x2="90" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="44" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="76" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="90" cy="60" r="7" class="pulse-ring" />
                <circle cx="90" cy="60" r="11" class="pulse-ring" />
                <line x1="90" y1="60" x2="230" y2="60" class="dashed-accent" />
                <line x1="230" y1="60" x2="370" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="230" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="300" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="360" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Live edge</strong>Renders latest position — freezes, then snaps forward.</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 400 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: delayed playback always interpolates smoothly, with no freeze or snap">
                <line x1="30" y1="60" x2="370" y2="60" class="baseline" />
                <circle cx="54" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="102" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="150" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="198" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="246" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="294" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
                <circle cx="342" cy="60" r="4" class="dot" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Delayed playback</strong>Always a real buffered window to interpolate through.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <span class="challenge-index">03</span>
          <strong>Keeping the UI responsive at startup</strong>
          <p>Parsing the initial fleet dataset and building vehicle records — up to 5,000 in the full system, 100 here — is heavy synchronous work that would otherwise hang the page while it loads; moved off the main thread into a Web Worker.</p>

          <div class="diagram-tiles diagram-tiles-2">
            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 400 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: parsing the fleet dataset blocks the main thread for the entire load">
                <line x1="30" y1="51" x2="370" y2="51" class="dashed" />
                <rect x="30" y="43" width="340" height="16" rx="3" class="busy" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Blocking</strong>Parsing thousands of records hangs the page on load.</figcaption>
            </figure>

            <figure class="diagram-tile">
              <svg class="diagram-svg" viewBox="0 0 400 100" role="img" aria-label="Diagram: after a brief handoff, a Web Worker parses off-thread while the main thread stays free">
                <rect x="30" y="35" width="36" height="10" rx="2" class="busy" />
                <line x1="66" y1="40" x2="370" y2="40" class="idle" />
                <line x1="66" y1="45" x2="66" y2="62" class="dashed" />
                <rect x="66" y="62" width="180" height="14" rx="3" class="worker" />
              </svg>
              <figcaption><strong>Off-thread</strong>A brief handoff, then parsing moves off the main thread.</figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-block">
          <span class="challenge-index">04</span>
          <strong>Rendering at scale</strong>
          <p>DOM-based markers (one element per vehicle, repositioned every frame) stop scaling past a few hundred vehicles; moved to GPU-based instanced rendering (deck.gl's IconLayer) to handle thousands without stalling the browser. Tested up to 5,000 (this demo's previous fleet size) — likely scales further, just not verified past that. Runs 100 here so individual behavior stays visible.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card-footer">
          <ul class="tags">
            {tags.map((tag) => <li>{tag}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  #work {
    padding: 6rem 0;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .card {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 16px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .card-body {
    padding: 1.75rem;
  }

  h3 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
  }

  .writeup {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 68ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
  }

  .feature-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .feature-block .challenge-index {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .feature-block strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--text);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .feature-block p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 68ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .feature-block > p {
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .diagram-tiles {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .diagram-tiles-4 {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  }

  .diagram-tiles-2 {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .diagram-tiles-4 {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .diagram-tiles-4,
    .diagram-tiles-2 {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .diagram-tile {
    margin: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 0.6rem;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .diagram-tile figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .diagram-tile figcaption strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
  }

  .diagram-svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  .diagram-svg .divider {
    stroke: var(--border);
    stroke-width: 1;
  }

  .diagram-svg .baseline {
    stroke: var(--accent);
    stroke-width: 2;
    fill: none;
  }

  .diagram-svg .dot {
    fill: var(--accent);
  }

  .diagram-svg .dot-rejected {
    fill: var(--bg-elevated);
    stroke: var(--text-muted);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }

  .diagram-svg .pulse-ring {
    fill: none;
    stroke: var(--text-muted);
    stroke-width: 1;
    stroke-dasharray: 2 2;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .diagram-svg .dashed {
    stroke: var(--text-muted);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    stroke-dasharray: 4 3;
    fill: none;
  }

  .diagram-svg .dashed-accent {
    stroke: var(--accent);
    stroke-width: 2;
    stroke-dasharray: 5 4;
    fill: none;
  }

  .diagram-svg .break-tick,
  .diagram-svg .reject-mark {
    stroke: var(--text-muted);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }

  .diagram-svg .busy {
    fill: var(--text-muted);
    opacity: 0.35;
    stroke: var(--text-muted);
    stroke-width: 1;
  }

  .diagram-svg .idle {
    stroke: var(--accent);
    stroke-width: 2;
  }

  .diagram-svg .worker {
    fill: var(--accent-soft);
    stroke: var(--accent);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }

  .card-footer {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .tags li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft);
    background: var(--accent-soft);
    border-radius: 999px;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
  }
</style>
